"n. 口水；v. 流口水；粗俗地表示 【英】 n.口水(saliva drooled from the mouth) n. 口水 = drool; v 流(口水) = drool 【记】slo = slow, bber读: ber－特别慢地打ber(打ber的意思是kiss), 很容易流口水. 【参】slaver(n 唾液; v 垂涎) 【记】slumber 睡觉时流口水；音：睡老伯，傻老伯，睡觉时的老伯或呆傻的老伯都是流口水的 【相关】slabber 是slobber的变体 slobber (v.)  c.1400, probably of imitative origin; compare Frisian slobberje ""to slurp,"" Middle Low German slubberen ""slurp,"" Middle Dutch overslubberen ""wade through a ditch."" Related: Slobbered; slobbering. As noun from c.1400 as ""mud, slime,"" 1755 as ""saliva."" Congreve has slabber (v.), from Middle Dutch slabberen."
